en_408925_0	HE M Ashraf Haidari, Ambassador of Afghanistan for Sri Lanka on Wednesday (5) paid a courtesy call on the Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake at the Army Headquarters, Colombo upon his recent assumption of office in Sri Lanka.
en_408925_1	The Ambassador was welcomed by Major General Ajith Wijesinghe, Military Secretary and Colonel Udaya Kumara, Military Assistant at the entrance to the Commander’s Secretariat.
en_408925_2	During the cordial meeting, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, and the visiting Afghanistan Ambassador exchanged views on bilateral matters of mutual interest with focus on ongoing Army-involved development roles.
en_408925_3	Towards the end of the friendly meeting, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake presented a memento to the envoy as a token of goodwill and understanding.
en_408925_4	He left his compliments in the Visitors’ Book before his exit.
